    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="original">
                <pb facs="EHRI-ET-JMP015_01.jpg" n="1"/>
                <p>Protokol</p>
                <p>sepsaný s <persName ref="#ehri_et_gibian_hanus" type="ehri">Hanušem <hi rend="letter-spacing: +2px">Gibianem</hi></persName>, nar.
                        <date when="1902-08-15">15. 8. 1902</date> v <placeName ref="#prague" type="ehri">Praze</placeName>, z <term ref="#t508"
                        type="subject">pracovního tábora</term>
                    <placeName ref="#l2026" type="camp">Nováky</placeName>, okr. <placeName ref="#okres-prievidza" type="ehri">Prijevica</placeName>,
                        <placeName ref="#slovak-republic" type="ehri">Slovensko</placeName>, bytem v <placeName ref="#prague" type="ehri">Praze
                        I.</placeName>, <placeName ref="#prague" type="ehri">Rybná</placeName> 8, národnosti <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_czechs"
                        type="subject">české</term>, povoláním bankovní úředník.</p>
                <p>Od roku <date when="1941">1941</date> do <date when="1944-09">září 1944</date> žil jsem se svojí dvoučlennou <term ref="#t819"
                        type="subject">rodinou</term> /: manželka a syn :/ v <term ref="#t508" type="subject">táboře</term>
                    <placeName ref="#l2026" type="camp">Nováky</placeName>, okres <placeName ref="#okres-prievidza" type="ehri">Prijevica</placeName>,
                        <placeName ref="#slovak-republic" type="ehri">Slovensko</placeName>. Tam jsem <term ref="#t556" type="subject">pracoval</term>
                    ve stavební správě. Byli jsme <term ref="#t837" type="subject">ubytování</term> v dřevěných barácích, <term ref="#t819"
                        type="subject">rodiny</term>
                    <term ref="#t837" type="subject">bydlely</term> pohromadě, svobodní zvlášť. <term ref="#t832" type="subject">Stravovací</term>
                    podmínky byly ucházející. <term ref="#t508" type="subject">Tábor</term> byl zpočátku pod dozorem <orgName ref="#g397" type="ehri"
                        >Hlinkovy gardy</orgName>, která se vyznačovala surovostí. Později byla <orgName ref="#g397" type="ehri">Hlinkova
                        garda</orgName> vystřídána <placeName ref="#slovak-republic" type="ehri">slovenskými</placeName>
                    <term ref="#t1125" type="subject">četníky</term>. V <date when="1944-09">září 1944</date>, začátkem <placeName
                        ref="#slovak-republic" type="ehri">slovenského</placeName>
                    <term ref="#t254" type="subject">povstání</term>, byl <term ref="#t508" type="subject">tábor</term> zrušen a <term ref="#t483"
                        type="subject">židovští občané</term> tohoto <term ref="#t508" type="subject">tábora</term> směli se volně pohybovati na
                    prostoru ovládaném <placeName ref="#slovak-republic" type="ehri">slovenskou</placeName>
                    <orgName ref="#g497" type="ehri">národní radou</orgName>.</p>
                <p>Následkem postupného obsazení <placeName ref="#slovak-republic" type="ehri">Slovenska</placeName>
                    <term ref="#g438" type="subject">německou armádou</term>
                    <term ref="#t204" type="subject">prchli</term> jsme s <term ref="#t819" type="subject">rodinou</term> do okolí <placeName
                        ref="#banska-bystrica" type="ehri">Banské Bystrice</placeName>, kde jsem až do <date when="1944-10-28">28. října 1944</date>
                    pracoval ve státní rafinerii v <placeName ref="#dubove" type="ehri">Dubové</placeName>. Když se <term ref="#g438" type="subject"
                        >německá armáda</term> blížila k <placeName ref="#banska-bystrica" type="ehri">Banské Bystrici</placeName>, byli jsme nuceni
                        <term ref="#t262" type="subject">ukrýti</term> se ve <placeName ref="#slovak-republic" type="ehri">slovenských</placeName>
                    horách. Po třídenním bloudění bez cíle, po kterém <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Němci</term> dvakrát
                    na nás stříleli, byli jsme <date when="1944-01-01">1. 11. 1944</date> chyceni. <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans"
                        type="subject">Němečtí</term>
                    <term ref="#t1216" type="subject">esesáci</term> soustředili nás na jedné louce, ptali se nás, zdali jsme Židé, přičemž lidé,
                    kteří se mohli vykázat <term ref="#t373" type="subject">árijskými</term> papíry, byli propuštěni. Židé byli vyzváni, ihned
                    odevzdat hodinky, peníze a všechno cenné, co měli při sobě, při čemž <term ref="#t1216" type="subject">esesáci</term> se
                    vyjádřili, že to už nebudeme potřebovat. Potom nás dal velitel <term ref="#t1216" type="subject">SS</term> odtransportovat
                    s upozorněním, že nás doprovodí hlídka 2 <term ref="#t1097" type="subject">vojáků</term>, a že se nám nic nestane. Cestou z hor
                    dolů přibyli ještě 4 <term ref="#t1216" type="subject">esesáci</term>, takže jich celkem bylo 6. Vedli nás na jednu louku, <term
                        ref="#t1216" type="subject">esesáci</term> zůstali pozadu a dali nám příkaz, abychom šli směrem na <placeName
                        ref="#banska-bystrica" type="ehri">Banskou Bystrici</placeName> a zůstali pohromadě. Když jsme se vzdálili asi 10 kroků,
                    začali na nás zezadu střílet. Stříleli tak dlouho, až všichni /: 42 osob :/ zůstali v <term ref="#t745" type="subject"
                        >mrtvém</term> neb polomrtvém stavu ležet. Pak prohlíželi každou jednotlivou osobu, vzali si ještě, co se jim líbilo, a <term
                        ref="#t745" type="subject">zavraždili</term> každého, kdo ještě nebyl úplně <term ref="#t745" type="subject">mrtev</term>
                    ranou do hlavy. Já jsem se vydal za <term ref="#t745" type="subject">mrtvého</term>, rovněž jedna 14 letá <term ref="#t824"
                        type="subject">holčička</term>, která byla přikryta pláštěm svého otce, zázrakem se zachránila. Bylo to <date
                        when="1944-11-01">1. listopadu 1944</date> ve 13 hodin v sedle mezi <placeName ref="#kozi-chrbat" type="ehri">Kozím
                        Chrbátem</placeName> a <placeName ref="#prasiva" type="ehri">Prašivou</placeName> v <placeName ref="#nizke-tatry" type="ehri"
                        >Nízkých Tatrách</placeName>, blízko obci <placeName ref="#hiadel" type="ehri">Hiadel</placeName>.</p>
                <p>Protokol přijala: Vlastnoruční podpis:</p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_kratkova_marta" type="ehri">Marta Kratková</persName></p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_gibian_hanus" type="ehri">Hanuš Gibian</persName></p>
                <p>Podpis svědků:</p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_gerzonova_berta" type="ehri">Berta Gerzonová</persName></p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_mull_jan" type="ehri">Jan Müll</persName>
                    <note type="gloss">uncertain</note></p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_weinberger_robert" type="ehri">Robert Weinberger</persName></p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_liewerand_karel" type="ehri">Karel Liewerand</persName></p>
                <p>Za archiv: <persName ref="#ehri_et_schmiedt_alexander" type="ehri">Alex. Schmiedt</persName></p>
                <p><term ref="#t657" type="subject">Dokumentační akce</term></p>
                <p><date when="1945-11-19">19. XI. 1945</date></p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev" type="ehri">Zeev Scheck</persName></p>
            </div>
            <div type="transcription">
                <pb facs="EHRI-ET-JMP015_01.jpg" n="1"/>
                <p>Statement</p>
                <p>written with <persName ref="#ehri_et_gibian_hanus" type="ehri">Hanuš <hi rend="letter-spacing: +2px">Gibian</hi></persName>, born
                        <date when="1902-08-15">15. 8. 1902</date> in <placeName ref="#prague" type="ehri">Prague</placeName>, in the <placeName
                        ref="#l2026" type="camp">Nováky</placeName> <term ref="#t508" type="subject">labor camp</term>, <placeName
                        ref="#okres-prievidza" type="ehri">Prijevica</placeName> district, <placeName ref="#slovak-republic" type="ehri"
                        >Slovakia</placeName>, residing in <placeName ref="#prague" type="ehri">Prague I.</placeName>, <placeName ref="#prague"
                        type="ehri">Rybná</placeName> 8, <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_czechs" type="subject">Czech</term> nationality, occupation
                    bank clerk.</p>
                <p>From <date when="1941">1941</date> to <date when="1944-09">September 1944</date>, I lived with my two-member <term ref="#t819"
                        type="subject">family</term> (wife and son) in the <placeName ref="#l2026" type="camp">Nováky</placeName> <term ref="#t508"
                        type="subject">camp</term>, <placeName ref="#okres-prievidza" type="ehri">Prijevica</placeName> district, <placeName
                        ref="#slovak-republic" type="ehri">Slovakia</placeName>. I <term ref="#t556" type="subject">worked</term> there in the
                    construction administration. We were <term ref="#t837" type="subject">housed</term> in wooden buildings; <term ref="#t819"
                        type="subject">families</term>
                    <term ref="#t837" type="subject">lived</term> together, the unmarried separately. The <term ref="#t832" type="subject">food</term>
                    was fair. At first, the <term ref="#t508" type="subject">camp</term> was supervised by <orgName ref="#g397" type="ehri">Hlinka’s
                        guards</orgName>, who were extremely cruel. Later, <orgName ref="#g397" type="ehri">Hlinka’s guards</orgName> were replaced by
                        <placeName ref="#slovak-republic" type="ehri">Slovak</placeName>
                    <term ref="#t1125" type="subject">policemen</term>. In <date when="1944-09">September 1944</date>, at the beginning of the
                        <placeName ref="#slovak-republic" type="ehri">Slovak</placeName>
                    <term ref="#t254" type="subject">uprising</term>, the <term ref="#t508" type="subject">camp</term> was abolished and the <term
                        ref="#t483" type="subject">Jewish inhabitants</term> of this <term ref="#t508" type="subject">camp</term> were allowed to move
                    freely throughout the space occupied by the <placeName ref="#slovak-republic" type="ehri">Slovak</placeName>
                    <orgName ref="#g497" type="ehri">National Council</orgName>.</p>
                <p>As a result of the gradual occupation of <placeName ref="#slovak-republic" type="ehri">Slovakia</placeName> by the <term
                        ref="#g438" type="subject">German army</term>, I <term ref="#t204" type="subject">escaped</term> together with my <term
                        ref="#t819" type="subject">family</term> to the area around <placeName ref="#banska-bystrica" type="ehri">Banská
                        Bystrica</placeName>, where I worked in the state refinery in <placeName ref="#dubove" type="ehri">Dubová</placeName> until
                        <date when="1944-10-28">October 28th 1944</date>. When the <term ref="#g438" type="subject">German army</term>
                        approached <placeName ref="#banska-bystrica" type="ehri">Banská Bystrica</placeName>, we were forced to <term ref="#t262"
                        type="subject">hide</term> in the <placeName ref="#slovak-republic" type="ehri">Slovak</placeName> mountains. After wandering
                    aimlessly for three whole days, during which the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Germans</term> twice
                    shot at us, we were captured on <date when="1944-11-01">1. 11. 1944</date>. <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans"
                        type="subject">German</term>
                    <term ref="#t1216" type="subject">SSmen</term> gathered all of us together in a meadow and asked us if we were Jews. Those who
                    could provide papers proving they were <term ref="#t373" type="subject">Aryan</term> were released. The Jews were told to
                    immediately hand over their watches, money, and all of the valuables that they had on them. The <term ref="#t1216" type="subject"
                        >SSmen</term> told us that we would no longer need them. Then, the <term ref="#t1216" type="subject">SS</term> leader ordered
                    us to be transported and notified us that a patrol of 2 <term ref="#t1097" type="subject">soldiers</term> would accompany us,
                    promising that nothing would happen to us. On our way down from the mountains, we were joined by 4 more <term ref="#t1216"
                        type="subject">SSmen</term>, so there was a total of 6. They took us to a meadow where the <term ref="#t1216" type="subject"
                        >SSmen</term> hung back and ordered us to walk toward <placeName ref="#banska-bystrica" type="ehri">Banská
                        Bystrica</placeName> and to stay together. After we had gone forward for about 10 steps, they began to shoot us in the back.
                    They fired until everyone (42 people) lay <term ref="#t745" type="subject">dead</term> or half-dead. They then examined each body
                    and took whatever they liked, and <term ref="#t745" type="subject">murdered</term> anyone who wasn’t <term ref="#t745"
                        type="subject">dead</term> yet with a shot to the dead. I pretended to be <term ref="#t745" type="subject">dead</term> as well
                    as a 14-year-old <term ref="#t824" type="subject">girl</term> who was covered by her father’s overcoat. By a miracle, she was
                    saved. This happened on <date when="1944-11-01">November 1st, 1944</date>, at 13:00 in the gap between <placeName
                        ref="#kozi-chrbat" type="ehri">Kozí Chrbát</placeName> and <placeName ref="#prasiva" type="ehri">Prašiva</placeName> in
                        the <placeName ref="#nizke-tatry" type="ehri">Lower Tatra Mountains</placeName>, near the village of <placeName ref="#hiadel"
                        type="ehri">Hiadel</placeName>.</p>
                <p>Signature:</p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_kratkova_marta" type="ehri">Marta Kratková</persName></p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_gibian_hanus" type="ehri">Hanuš Gibian</persName></p>
                <p>Signatures of witnesses:</p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_gerzonova_berta" type="ehri">Berta Gerzonová</persName></p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_mull_jan" type="ehri">Jan Müll</persName>
                    <note type="gloss">uncertain</note></p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_weinberger_robert" type="ehri">Robert Weinberger</persName></p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_liewerand_karel" type="ehri">Karel Liewerand</persName></p>
                <p>On behalf of the archive: <persName ref="#ehri_et_schmiedt_alexander" type="ehri">Alex. Schmiedt</persName></p>
                <p><term ref="#t657" type="subject">Documentation campaign</term></p>
